All of us â Parliament, Commission and Council â must be at all times capable of that sort of self-criticism, for whenever human rights are at stake, when people are tortured, when their rights are trodden underfoot â as they are in many countries â then what that means is that we, who are tasked with the defence of human rights, are not doing enough.
That is why we need to give constant thought to how we could improve our performance, and what this debate has done is to help us to do just that.
A range of issues have been addressed, and I would just like to touch very briefly on one or two of them.
